article.headline: Youngstown State 95, Slippery Rock 57
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Keston Roberts had 22 points and five other Youngstown State players reached double-digits to give the Penguins a 95-57 win over Slippery Rock on Sunday night. Roberts shot 8-of-14 from the floor and had nine rebounds for Youngstown State (2-2). Jack Liles added 16 points and nine rebounds and John Barber and Byron Davis each had 14 points. Youngstown State shot 59 percent (33-of-56) from the floor while holding Division II Slippery Rock to 39 percent (23-of-59), and the Penguins outrebounded the Rock 43-20. George Cotal had 12 points for the Penguins, and Quin Humphrey added 10. Brandon Thompson led Slippery Rock (0-1) with 16 points, Kenny Smith had 10 and Glenn Reepmeyer added 13 points and nine rebounds.
